Description:
    Configure Faultline to use a dedicated database instead of the primary
    application database. This keeps error tracking and APM data separate
    from your business data.

Example:
    rails generate faultline:database

    This will:
    - Show instructions for adding database configuration to database.yml
    - Update config/initializers/faultline.rb with database_key setting

Options:
    --database-key  The database key to use (default: "faultline")

Example with custom key:
    rails generate faultline:database --database-key=errors
